<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-09-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="113" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Vasquez</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the Dominican Republic</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mew York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-14"><hi rend="italic">September 14, 1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In the name of my Government and of myself I offer sincerest sympathy and
                            condolence upon the death of His Excellency President McKinley, who knew
                            how to command the admiration of the whole world.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">F. Leonte Vasquez</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Chargé d’Affaires, Dominican
                                Republic.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>